main event: A cigar-shaped, red object was observed for approximately 6 seconds over Rice, Washington.
interesting points: The object was described as being approximately 15 feet long and emitting a light exhaust in the form of a spray.
The object was observed by a 69-year-old farmer in Rice, Washington, who was described as very reliable and not a drinker.
The object was seen just above the horizon and then disappeared at the horizon, traveling in a straight and level flight.
The sighting was also reported by the farmer's wife.
The weather conditions were generally good in the area at the time of the sighting.
